        </statement>
      </exercise>

      <blockquote style="border: 1px; border-style: solid; color: gray;">
        <p><q>Now the science of mathematics is very important.  This book ...therefore will be of great benefit to the people of the world.  The knowledge for investigation, the development of intellectual power, the way of controlling the kingdom and of ruling even  the whole world, can be obtained by those who are able to make good use of this book.  Ought not those who have great desire to be learned take this with them and study it with great care?</q></p>
        <attribution>Zhu Shijie (JOO shoor-jieh), China, 1303.  <cite>The introduction to Precious Mirror of the Four Elements</cite></attribution>
      </blockquote>
      <exercise xml:id="exercise-god-math-9" workspace=".5in">
