      </exercise>
    </page>

    <page xml:id="god-math-worksheet-p2">
      <blockquote>
        <p><q>Since geometry is co-eternal with the divine mind before the birth of things, God himself served as his own model in creating the world (for what is there in God which is not God?), and he with his own image reached down to humanity. </q></p>
        <attribution>Johannes Kepler, 1619.  <cite>The Harmony of the World</cite></attribution>
      </blockquote>
      <exercise xml:id="exercise-god-math-11" workspace=".5in">
